title: Woman dies after accidental self-inflicted gunshot
content:
A Houston woman staying in Monroe died from an accidental self-inflicted gunshot wound Sunday night.
The victim has been identified as Vanquisha Mitchell, 21.
According to the Monroe Police Department, Mitchell was handling a handgun located in a home on McCall Street at shortly before 9 p.m. when she pulled the trigger and died as the result of a single gunshot wound to the head.
